definition.value: Organ with organ cavity which connects the renal sinus to the urinary bladder. Examples: There are only two ureters, the right and the left ureters.
Organ with organ cavity which connects the cavity of the middle ear to the cavity of the pharynx. Examples: There are only two pharyngotympanic tubes, the right and the left pharyngotympanic tubes.
Organ component which has as its parts the muscle fiber and the endomysium.
Striated muscle cell which has as its direct parts two or more peripherally located nuclei.
Reticular tissue which surrounds a muscle cell.
Structural relation which holds between an anatomical structure and some organizational pattern.
Parietal serous membrane which is continuous with the visceral pleura and is attached to the dome of the diaphragm.
Visceral serous membrane which is continuous with the parietal pleura and is attached to the parenchyma of lobe of lung.
Cavity of serous sac surropunded by the pleura.
